<HEAD>Outage Sparks Fights, Confusion at Beach Resort</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEASIDE HEIGHTS, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   People smashed windows and fights
erupted early today when a power outage blacked out this beach
resort, but no injuries were reported, police said.
   Sgt. Louis A Koehler of the Dover Township Police Department
said people began to run along the boardwalk in all directions
after the power failed at 12:52 a.m. Scores of police in riot gear
responded, blocking the bridge leading to the island community and
evacuating people from the boardwalk.
   Koehler said police and firemen from Seaside Park, Dover, Brick,
Lakewood and Manchester townships were called in.
   Some people were stuck on amusement rides, but police helped
them off, he said.
   It was unclear how many people were on the boardwalk when power
failed.
   The outage occurred when a substation transformer of the Jersey
Central Power &amp; Light Co. failed, said a company spokesman, James
F. Lowney.
