<SECOND>PM-Iran-Drugs,0151</SECOND>
<HEAD>41 Drug Smugglers, Brothel Organizers Hanged</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Forty-one drug smugglers and brothel
keepers were hanged in Tehran and the northeastern provincial
capital of Mashad, Iran's official news agency said today.
   The Islamic Republic News Agency, monitored in Nicosia, said the
executions took place Friday and today.
   The 17 executed in Mashad were hanged in public, the agency said.
   In Tehran, 10 men and 11 women were hanged in Qasr prison, with
the remaining three hanged in a square ``in front of the public in
southern Tehran,'' it said.
   Those hanged in Tehran ``were involved for years in drug
trafficking and organized prostitution,'' said a statement by the
Islamic Revolutionary Court, which handed down the sentences, IRNA
reported.
   Those executed in Mashad had been convicted of selling,
distributing and possessing ``200 sacks of opium and tens of kilos
of heroin,'' it said.
