<FIRST>r i PM-Switzerland-Chess     08-05 0199</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Switzerland-Chess,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ivanchuk Wins Grandmaster Tourney</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BIENNE, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soviet favorite Vasily Ivanchuk won
the grandmaster tournament at the 22nd Bienne Chess Festival after
a final-round victory over Ferdinand Hellers of Sweden.
   Lev Polugaevsky of the Soviet Union finished level with Ivanchuk
on points as the 14-round tourney ended late Friday. But the
world's third-ranked player was ahead due to a higher total of
Sonneborn-Berger points, a fine ranking used for tiebreaks.
   The 20-year-old Ivanchuk, playing white, attacked with gusto to
defeat Hellers in 40 moves and secure his first Bienne title.
Polugaevsky, 54, needed 53 moves to beat Nick de Firmian of the
United States in his last-round match.
   Ivan Sokolov, co-winner of last year's tournament, posted a
surprise win over U.S. player Anthony Miles to capture third place.
   Results:
   _ Vlastimil Hort, West Germany - Eugenio Torre, Philippines,
0.5-0.5
   _ Anthony Miles, United States - Ivan Sokolov, Yugoslavia, 0-1
   _ Vasily Ivanchuk, Soviet Union - Ferdinand Hellers, Sweden, 1-0
   _ Nick de Firmian, United States - Lev Polugaevsky, Soviet
Union, 0-1
   Final standings:
   Ivanchuk, 9 points (29 SB), Polugaevsky 9 (27.5 SB), Sokolov, 8,
Hort, 7, Miles, 7, Torre, 6, De Firmian, 5.5, Hellers, 4.5.
