<HEAD>Landslide Buries 45 Bus Passengers; All Feared Dead</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with two grafs to UPDATE with 22 sted 20 bodies recovered;
pickup graf three pvs `All those...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A landslide Saturday buried about 45
people who had left passenger buses to clear boulders blocking a
mountain road in northern India, and all were believed dead, news
reports said.
   State-run television said at least 22 bodies had been recovered.
Rescuers were using bulldozers, Press Trust of India said.
   All those buried were feared dead, the agency reported. It also
said 15 people were hospitalized.
   The accident occurred 185 miles north of New Delhi on a national
highway connecting India with Tibet.
   Passengers had left the two buses to clear the road when more
rocks and boulders crashed down on them, Press Trust of India said.
A truck loaded with apples also was buried.
