<DATELINE>NARBONNE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Torrential rains flooded the streets of
this city in southern France on Saturday, stranding more 150 people
in their cars, officials said.
   Firefighters said they rescued 150 to 300 people _ some by boat
_ from vehicles trapped in rapidly rising water in lower-lying
sections of Narbonne, a city near the Mediterranean and 530 miles
south of Paris.
   A fire brigade in Narbonne, quoting the national weather
service, said from 4 to 6 inches of rain fell Saturday afternoon.
Earlier reports had incorrectly put the downpour at 31 inches.
   After the downpour stopped, the waters receded and life quickly
returned to normal.
